# ==============================================================================
# SpectraMind V50 — DVC Ignore Rules
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Purpose:
#   • Prevents DVC from accidentally tracking ephemeral or environment files
#   • Keeps the DVC DAG clean, reproducible, and Kaggle/CI-safe
#   • Complements .gitignore — this applies only to DVC tracking scope
# ==============================================================================

# ───────────────────────── Python Build Artifacts ─────────────────────────
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
**/*.pyd
**/*.so
**/*.dll
**/*.dylib
**/*.egg-info/
*.egg
dist/
build/

# ───────────────────────── Notebook / Editor Junk ─────────────────────────
**/.ipynb_checkpoints/
**/*.swp
**/*.swo
**/*.tmp
**/*.bak

# ───────────────────────── Logs & Run Artifacts ─────────────────────────
logs/**
wandb/**             # Weights & Biases run logs
mlruns/**            # MLflow tracking runs
tensorboard/**       # Local tensorboard event files
.dvc/tmp/**          # DVC’s own temp dirs (don’t recurse into cache)
.dvc/exp/**          # Experiment scratch space

# ───────────────────────── Environment / Dependency Files ─────────────────
.venv/**
.env
.env.*
.conda_env/
Pipfile
Pipfile.lock
poetry.lock
pyproject.toml
requirements*.txt

# ───────────────────────── Kaggle / Competition Artifacts ─────────────────
kaggle_work/**
kaggle_notebooks/**
kaggle_submissions/**
kaggle_cache/**

# ───────────────────────── OS / IDE Noise ─────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/**
.vscode/**
*.log

# ───────────────────────── Safety Notes ─────────────────────────
# DVC will ignore these patterns; Git may still see them unless in .gitignore.
# Ensure pipeline data (data/, outputs/, models/, artifacts/) are tracked ONLY via DVC.
# ==============================================================================